    <body>
        <sect1>
            <title>Earth Elemental</title>

            <para>
                Elementals of earth are probably the most common sort, for
                they are easy to summon and control, and are readily
                formed from earth, mud, sand or rock - all of which are
                plentiful in all places except the high seas.
            </para>

            <para>
                Elementals of earth are also the most common to be found
                in the wild, for sometimes a great spilling of blood can
                awaken the spirits of the ground, which take it as a
                sacrifice to power their form. Such free-willed spirits
                are known as <e>goblins</e>.
            </para>
        </sect1>

        <sect1>
            <title>Elemental Bestiary</title>

            <bestiary role="bestiary" title="Earth Elementals">
                <beast name="Earth Elemental" primary="true">
                    <information>
                        <type>Elemental</type>
                        <demeanor>Unintelligent</demeanor>

                        <habitat climate="Any" terrain="Any"
                                 frequency="very rare"/>

                        <origin>Habisfern</origin>
                        <genre>Fantasy</genre>
                    </information>

                    <description>
                        <short>
                            Earth elementals are creatures of earth and
                            rock.
                        </short>

                        <physical>
                            <para>
                                Earth elementals may be formed of many
                                different materials, and this effects their
                                physical properties. The strongest are of
                                rock, the weakest of sand or mud.
                            </para>

                            <para>
                                The statistics given below assume that the
                                elementals are formed from Earth. If they
                                are formed from sand or mud, then their
                                soak is halved, if they are formed from
                                rock, then add 50% to their soak.
                            </para>
                        </physical>
                    </description>
                </beast>

                <beast name="Earth Elemental I">
                    <information>
                        <type>Elemental</type>
                        <demeanor>Unintelligent</demeanor>

                        <habitat climate="Any" terrain="Any"
                                 frequency="very rare"/>

                        <origin>Habisfern</origin>
                        <genre>Fantasy</genre>
                    </information>

                    <description>
                        <short>
                            Earth elementals are creatures of earth and
                            rock.
                        </short>

                        <physical>
                            <para>
                                The smallest and weakest of the earth
                                elementals, this type are sometimes known
                                as imps. They have the appearance of a
                                small monkey, with stony skin, black eyes,
                                sharp claws and a very human face.
                            </para>
                        </physical>
                    </description>

                    <statistics xmlns="http://yagsbook.sourceforge.net/xml/yags">
                        <attributes size="2" soak="10">
                            <attribute name="strength" score="1"/>
                            <attribute name="stamina" score="5"/>
                            <attribute name="agility" score="4"/>
                            <attribute name="dexterity" score="2"/>
                            <attribute name="perception" score="2"/>
                            <attribute name="intelligence" score="*"/>
                            <attribute name="charisma" score="1"/>
                            <attribute name="will" score="2"/>
                        </attributes>

                        <skills>
                            <group name="Talents" type="talents">
                                <skill name="Athletics" score="5"/>
                                <skill name="Awareness" score="2"/>
                                <skill name="Brawl" score="4"/>
                                <skill name="Charm" score="1"/>
                                <skill name="Guile" score="1"/>
                                <skill name="Sleight" score="4"/>
                                <skill name="Stealth" score="5"/>
                                <skill name="Throw" score="1"/>
                            </group>
                        </skills>

                        <combat>
                            <combatstyle style="Claw" skill="Brawl">
                                <attack attribute="agility" bonus="+0"/>
                                <defence attribute="agility" bonus="+0"/>
                                <damage type="mixed" bonus="+1"/>
                            </combatstyle>
                        </combat>

                        <passions>
                            <passion name="Bravery" score="10"/>
                            <passion name="Ego" score="1"/>
                            <passion name="Restraint" score="1"/>
                            <passion name="Temperance" score="1"/>
                        </passions>

                        <advantages>
                            <advantage name="Elemental"/>
                        </advantages>
                    </statistics>
                </beast>

                <beast name="Earth Elemental II">
                    <information>
